> Concept: only pursue investment from investors who are willing to commit x% of their investment into a climate initiative of your choosing. Do I really want to take money from someone who doesn't care about the fate of our world?
@theonlyjohnny 

This is a really interesting idea. Though, there's a good argument to say that not all investors should be in the space and it's okay to specialize. The much tougher, but arguably more impactful route, is LPs. If a VC manages money for LPs that are super cozy with the fossil fuel industry, those are LPs that I don't want to make money for.

